File: COVID-19 test. AFP/Michael Ciaglo JOHANNESBURG - The deadly COVID-19 variant wreaking havoc in India has been detected in Uganda.
Uganda’s Health Ministry says this should serve as a wake-up call and is urging citizens to continue exercising safety measures. The variant spreads faster and causes more severe illness in younger people. READ: Bodies pile up as COVID-19 overwhelms India The discovery comes just days after Uganda's neighbour, Kenya suspended flights to and from India for two weeks. India has recorded over 200,000 COVID-19 deaths. On Wednesday, the country recorded the highest number of cases reported in a single day across the world.